text: Stillwater is an unincorporated community in King County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Stillwater was established in 1910, and remained in operation until 1925. The community was named after Stillwater, Minnesota, the native home of a large share of local loggers. ==References== ==External links== *Stillwater Elementary School Category:Unincorporated communities in King County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Stillwater, Washington
